ZH: 我站在窗前，朝向大海。
EN: I stand by the window, facing the sea.

ZH: 这座建筑朝向东方。
EN: This building faces east.

ZH: 他脸朝向地面，不敢看向天空。
EN: He faced the ground and dare not look up at the sky.

ZH: 我们应该朝向阳光走去。
EN: We should walk towards the sunshine.

ZH: 现代人更多地朝向城市发展。
EN: Modern people tend to develop towards cities.

ZH: 碧蓝的湖水朝向蓝天相连。
EN: The blue lake connects to the blue sky.

ZH: 他沉默不语，目光朝向远方。
EN: He remained silent, his gaze fixed on the distance.

ZH: 在西方文化中，佛像朝向东方。
EN: In Western culture, Buddha statues face east.

ZH: 学生们迎着朝阳走进校园。
EN: The students walked into the campus facing the morning sun.

ZH: 这扇窗户朝向北方，凉风常常从那里吹进来。
EN: This window faces north, and cool breeze often comes from there.

ZH: 她朝向观众微笑致意。
EN: She smiled and gestured towards the audience.

ZH: 这条街道朝向市中心延伸。
EN: This street extends towards the city center.

ZH: 每天早晨，他都喜欢朝向东方做瑜伽。
EN: Every morning, he likes to do yoga facing east.

ZH: 他们把家庭的神明朝向南方。
EN: They place the household gods facing the south.

ZH: 爬山的人常常朝向山顶努力攀登。
EN: Climbers often strive to climb towards the mountaintop.

ZH: 请你朝向前方走。
EN: Please walk towards the front.

ZH: 在这个城市，大多数建筑物朝向西方。
EN: In this city, most buildings face west.

ZH: 他喜欢在日出时望向海上。
EN: He likes to look out at the sea at sunrise.

ZH: 汽车行驶的方向朝向南方。
EN: The car is heading south.

ZH: 她用力朝向远处投掷石子。
EN: She threw a stone forcefully towards the distance.
